CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 5, 1961, pg. 12 reads: "Compete For Title -Guests of honor at the Frappe Sip sponsored by the Original D.I. CLub last Sunday were these contestants for the title of "Miss GPIL." Left to right, front row: Elexis Moore, Ellen Grinage, Cheryl Davis, Beverly White, Phyllis Gibson and Joyce Kirksey. Back row: Mrs. Helen Smalley and Mrs. Ella Carter, sponsors of the girls, and Miss Mabel Rodgers, contest chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of contestants for "Miss GPIL" contest, front row from left: Elexis Moore, Ellen Grinage, Cheryl Davis, Beverly White, Phyllis Gibson and Joyce Kirksey; back row: sponsors Helen Smalley and Ella Carter, and Mabel Rodgers, posed in front of Nellie Barron's home for DI Club and Greater Pittsburgh Improvement League (GPIL) Frappe Sip, Grotto Street
